<!-- INTRO -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="intro-grid">
      <div class="intro-body">
        <p class="section-number">01 — About This Service</p>
        <h2 class="section-title">LA's bar, restaurant, and wine culture demands refrigeration that performs precisely — and gets fixed fast when it doesn't.</h2>

        <p>Los Angeles has one of the densest concentrations of bars, craft cocktail lounges, wine bars, and hotel beverage programs in the US. West Hollywood alone has more liquor-licensed establishments per block than most cities have in their entire downtown. These operations depend on back-bar coolers, undercounter refrigerators, wine coolers, and kegerators that hold precise temperatures — not "cold enough," but within the 2–3°F range that proper beverage service and wine storage requires.</p>

        <p>We repair the full range of bar and beverage refrigeration: back-bar coolers and undercounter units in commercial bars and restaurants, wine coolers and wine refrigerators in both commercial and residential settings, kegerators and draft beer systems (refrigeration side), and specialty beverage coolers. Perlick and U-Line are the dominant premium brands in LA's high-end bar market; True and Beverage-Air are the workhorses in commercial back-bar applications. We service all of them, EPA 608 certified for any refrigerant work.</p>

        <p>This page also covers wine cooler repair specifically — GSC data shows LA operators searching this term hundreds of times monthly with no dedicated repair resource. Whether it's a commercial wine cooler in a Beverly Hills restaurant, a thermoelectric wine fridge in a Malibu home, or a back-bar wine cooler in a Silver Lake wine bar, we handle it the same day.</p>
      </div>

