<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">09 — Frequently Asked Questions</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Bar refrigerator &amp; wine cooler repair — what LA operators ask us</h2>

    <div class="faq-list">
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>How much does wine cooler or bar refrigerator repair cost in Los Angeles?</h3>
        <p>Diagnostic is $120, applied to repair if approved. Most repairs run $150–$450. Thermostat, fan motor, door gasket, Peltier module, or condenser cleaning is in this range. Compressor or refrigerant work runs $300–$650+. Written estimate before any work begins.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>What's the difference between thermoelectric and compressor wine coolers for repair?</h3>
        <p>Thermoelectric uses a solid-state Peltier module — quiet, no vibration, but limited cooling capacity. When it fails, the issue is usually the Peltier module or control board. Compressor units use a standard refrigeration system — more powerful, but louder. They fail like any refrigerator: condenser, compressor, refrigerant. Tell us your unit type when you call so we bring the right parts.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>My bar refrigerator is not cooling — what's the most common cause?</h3>
        <p>Dirty condenser coils — particularly in under-bar enclosed installations where airflow is restricted. In LA's dusty environment, under-bar condensers accumulate fouling 2–3× faster than freestanding units. Check that the condenser vent isn't blocked before calling. If clear and the unit still isn't cooling, call us at {phone}.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>My kegerator isn't keeping draft beer cold enough — can you fix it?</h3>
        <p>Yes — the refrigeration side. We repair compressor, thermostat, fan motor, and door gasket on kegerators. CO2 regulator and faucet hardware is operator-maintained; we assess on-site and distinguish refrigeration issues from dispensing system issues.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>Do you repair Perlick, U-Line, and Marvel bar refrigerators?</h3>
        <p>Yes. Perlick, U-Line, and Marvel are our most common LA premium bar refrigerator brands. True and Beverage-Air for commercial back-bar. Sub-Zero Wine, Liebherr, and Eurocave for premium wine storage. EPA 608 certified for all refrigerant work.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>My thermoelectric wine cooler isn't getting cold enough in summer — is it broken?</h3>
        <p>Not necessarily. Thermoelectric units can only cool approximately 20–25°F below ambient temperature. If LA summer ambient around the unit reaches 85–90°F (common in garages and unconditioned outdoor spaces), a functioning thermoelectric unit physically cannot reach 55°F. We'll test the module function and advise honestly — sometimes the answer is a different type of unit for the installation, not a repair.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

